  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the effect of docosahexaenoic acid (DHA, 22:6n-3)
      in improving cognitive functions in subjects with age-related cognitive decline. DHA is a
      long chain omega-3 fatty acid (LC-PUFA) that plays an important role in neural and visual
      development and cardiovascular health.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
